Skincare Product Description Guidelines for Shopify

Primary Goals:
    1. Educate and convert real customers with clear, benefit-focused content.
    2. Rank in search engines by matching real user intent with optimized, high-quality SEO content.

Critical Requirements:
    • Accuracy first: All information must be 100% verifiable from the official manufacturer source. No assumptions or added claims unless explicitly supported.
    • Skincare only: These guidelines apply only to skincare products (serums, moisturizers, toners, eye creams, sunscreens, exfoliants, masks, essences, acne treatments, etc.). Do not apply to makeup, hair care, body care, tools, oral care, or fragrance—those require separate instructions.
    • Language versions:
        – English version is required by default.
        – Arabic version is created only if (a) explicitly requested and (b) provided with the exact Arabic product name.

⸻

1. Process Overview
    1. Confirm category: Ensure the product is a skincare product.
    2. Keyword research: Build the English keyword list before writing. Include brand variations, high-intent search phrases, product type, skin concerns, and benefits.
    3. Write description: Follow the structure below exactly, starting with the SEO-focused opening paragraph.
    4. Supplementary SEO elements: Create Title, Meta Description, Tags, Alt Text, and Tips/Warnings based on the same source.
    5. Review/verify: Run through the final verification checklist.
    6. Arabic version (if applicable): Only after both conditions are met, adapt the content into Arabic following the parallel structure (Arabic version has its own requirements, not included here unless requested).

⸻

2. Writing and Formatting Rules
    • Tone & purpose: Clear, helpful, benefit-oriented, professional. Use accurate terminology. Avoid fluff, vague hype, or unsupported superlatives unless the brand copy uses them exactly.
    • Headings: Use <strong> only for section titles.
    • Paragraphs: Default size; do not manually change font size or use inline style.
    • HTML structure:
        – Use <strong> for headings.
        – Use <ul class="-mt-1 list-disc space-y-2 pl-8"> with <li class="whitespace-normal break-words"> for bullet lists (Key Benefits, Skin Types, Skin Concerns, etc.).
        – Use <ol class="-mt-1 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-8"> for step-by-step usage.
        – Use <br> or <br><br> consistently to separate major sections for readability.
        – No inline styles, no color definitions, no data-mce-style attributes.
    • Keyword inclusion: Do not start writing the description until the English keyword list is complete and reflects realistic customer search behavior.
    • Tags (even if Arabic) must be separated with English commas (,) because Shopify interprets each comma-separated token as a distinct tag; non-English commas or other separators break tagging.

⸻

3. SEO Keyword Rules
    • Build a focused keyword list before writing. Include:
        – Brand name + common misspellings/variants (spacing, transliteration, case-insensitive).
        – Product type (e.g., "hydrating face serum," "non-comedogenic moisturizer").
        – Skin concerns the product targets (e.g., "dark spots treatment," "dry skin serum").
        – Benefits/results (e.g., "brightening," "pore-minimizing," "dewy glow").
        – Intent combinations: brand + concern, product + format + benefit (e.g., "Korean vitamin C serum for hyperpigmentation").
    • Avoid overly broad single-word keywords like "skincare" alone; prioritize mid/high-intent descriptive phrases.
    • The first sentence of the description must naturally include: brand name, product type, and at least one high-intent keyword phrase.

⸻

4. Description Structure (English) — everything below goes inside a single code block for easy copy/paste, no extra title labels inside the block except the product content itself:

```html
[Opening paragraph: 80–180 words. Include brand name, product type, and one or more high-intent skincare keyword phrases naturally. Explain who the product is for, what it does, how it works (core mechanism), and what differentiates it. Benefit-focused, readable, not stuffed.]

<br><br>

<strong>Key Benefits</strong>

<ul class="-mt-1 list-disc space-y-2 pl-8">
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">Benefit 1 (clear outcome, e.g., reduces redness and irritation)</li>
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">Benefit 2 (e.g., boosts hydration for plumper skin)</li>
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">Benefit 3 (e.g., improves texture and minimizes pores)</li>
    <!-- Add 3–7 outcome-focused benefits -->
</ul>

<br>

<strong>Skin Types</strong> <!-- This section applies only to skincare or Bodycare products -->

<ul class="-mt-1 list-disc space-y-2 pl-8">
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">[Only applicable: All skin types / Dry / Oily / Combination / Sensitive / Normal]</li>
</ul>

<br>

<strong>Skin Concerns</strong> <!-- This section applies only to skincare or Bodycare products -->

<ul class="-mt-1 list-disc space-y-2 pl-8">
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">[Relevant concerns, e.g., dehydration, hyperpigmentation, aging, dullness, acne, uneven tone]</li>
</ul>

<br>

<strong>How to Use</strong>

<!-- If discrete steps: -->
<ol class="-mt-1 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-8">
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">Step 1 (e.g., apply after cleansing and toning in the morning)</li>
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">Step 2 (e.g., follow with sunscreen for daytime protection)</li>
    <!-- Additional steps if needed -->
</ol>

<br><br> <!-- ALWAYS include this gap before Ingredients when using a list -->

<br> <!-- Or, if not using step list -->

[Write as a single paragraph noting time of use (morning/evening), layering order, frequency, and any prep/post notes.]

<br><br> <!-- ALWAYS include this gap before Ingredients when using a paragraph -->

<strong>Ingredients:</strong> [Full official INCI list / Title Case, comma-separated, in the order given by manufacturer.]

<br>

<strong>Set Contents:</strong> <!-- This section applies only to set or bundle products -->
<ol class="-mt-1 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-8">
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">product 1 (e.g., product 1 50ml)</li>
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">product 2 (e.g., product 2 100ml)</li>
    <li class="whitespace-normal break-words">product 3 (e.g., product 3 80ml)</li>

⸻

5. Supplementary SEO & Conversion Fields (each of these should be in copyable code blocks with no internal labels like “Page Title:”—just the content exactly as it should be pasted)

Tips and Warnings (2–4 actionable, context-aware entries; examples):

Use in the evening when layering with retinol.  
Apply sunscreen during the day if using AHAs/BHAs.  
Patch test before full use if skin is sensitive.  
Start gradually with high-concentration actives.

Tags (comma-separated, real search behavior, include brand variants, product type, concern, benefit, common misspellings, transliterations):

hydrating face serum, vitamin c serum, dark spot corrector, glowing skin, anti-aging serum, brightening serum, sensitive skin moisturizer, brandname skincare

• Always use English commas (,) even if the tag text is Arabic or transliterated.
• Do not overstuff—prioritize realistic high-intent variations.

Page Title (60–70 characters, starts with brand, includes product name and primary benefit/feature):

BrandName Vitamin C Serum | Brightening & Even Tone

Meta Description (140–155 characters; include brand, product type, key benefit or ingredient; stop at ~155):

BrandName Vitamin C Serum brightens dark spots and evens skin tone with lightweight antioxidant-rich formula for a radiant, glowing complexion.

Media Alt Text (5 variations, each under 125 characters, include brand + product + key feature):

BrandName Vitamin C Serum for Brightening  
Hydrating Face Serum by BrandName with Hyaluronic Acid  
BrandName Anti-Aging Serum for Fine Lines  
Lightweight Glow Serum BrandName for Uneven Skin Tone  
BrandName Skin Plumping Serum with Peptides

⸻
6. Categorization (Shopify fields)

Shopify Category:

[most specific, e.g., Health & Beauty > Personal Care > Cosmetics > Skin Care > Face Serums]

Product Type:

e.g., Serum / Moisturizer / Toner / Eye Cream / Sunscreen / Exfoliant

Collections:
• Select only from the approved internal collection hierarchy.
• If the needed collection is not present, do not guess or create; flag for review or request addition to the master list.
• A product may belong to multiple collections only if it legitimately fits each; avoid over-assigning.
• The chosen collection must exactly match spelling and hierarchy from the official list.

Example correct:

SKIN CARE > Serum & Treatments > Face Serum
K-BEAUTY > Korean Skin Care

Example incorrect (should be flagged):

SKIN CARE > Serums  (if "Serums" is not defined in approved list)

Skin Types:
• This section applies only to skincare products.
• Include only if the official product description supports it or the General Skin Types Rule explicitly applies.
• Choose exclusively from the approved list: All skin types, Dry, Oily, Combination, Sensitive, Normal.
• If not supported, omit this field entirely—do not guess, approximate, or leave placeholders.

Key Ingredients:
• Include **only if** the brand/source emphasizes them in the official description.  
• Select **exclusively** from the approved key ingredients (e.g., Niacinamide, Hyaluronic Acid, Vitamin C, Retinol, Ceramides, Peptides, Centella Asiatica, AHA/BHA, Panthenol, Green Tea, Shea Butter, Jojoba Oil, etc.).  
• Do not add ingredients not directly supported by the source; omit the entire field if none qualify.

Product Highlights:
• Include **only if** the official description explicitly lists or implies them.  
• Select **only** from the approved highlights: Vegan, Cruelty Free, Fragrance Free, Non-Comedogenic, Dermatologically Tested, Oil Free, Alcohol Free, Paraben Free, Sulfate Free.  
• Do not infer or add based on assumption; omit the field if none apply.

Skin Concerns:
• Include **only if** the product is marketed against specific concerns in the official source.  
• Choose **exclusively** from the approved Skin Concerns list (e.g., Dryness, Hyperpigmentation, Fine Lines, Acne, Redness, Enlarged Pores, etc.).  
• If no concerns are clearly targeted, omit this field completely.

