⸻
	8.	Final Verification Checklist (before publishing)
• Is the product correctly identified as skincare?
• Is the English keyword list complete and reflected in the copy (especially opening sentence)?
• Does the first sentence include brand name, product type, and high-intent keyword(s)?
• Is the opening paragraph 80–180 words, clear on audience, function, mechanism, and differentiation?
• Are only applicable Skin Types and Skin Concerns included (no irrelevant ones)?
• Are Key Benefits specific, outcome-focused, and clear?
• Is the How to Use section precise about routine placement, frequency, and layering?
• Are Ingredients formatted correctly (INCI/title case, comma-separated in official order)?
• Are Tips/Warnings actionable, contextual, and not generic?
• Is the Page Title within 60–70 characters and keyword-optimized?
• Is the Meta Description 140–155 characters, compelling, and includes key elements?
• Are Tags reflective of search behavior, comma-separated with English commas?
• Are Alt Texts varied, descriptive, under 125 characters, and include brand+product+feature?
• Is Shopify Category specific and correct?
• Are Collections accurate, applicable, and not excessive?
• No unsupported claims or irrelevant fields included.
• Formatting rules followed: only headings bolded, spacing with  as required, proper list classes, no inline styling.

⸻

Notes:
• If a required collection or taxonomy entry is missing, flag it instead of guessing.
• Do not include internal labels (like “Page Title:”) inside code blocks for SEO fields—present raw values for direct pasting.
• Keep English commas for any tag list even when tags are in Arabic script.
• Maintain human readability; SEO optimization should feel natural, not forced.

